{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For all of the vector types ("},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftTracer\/documentation\/SwiftTracer\/Color","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":","},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftTracer\/documentation\/SwiftTracer\/Vec2","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"  "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftTracer\/documentation\/SwiftTracer\/Vec3","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftTracer\/documentation\/SwiftTracer\/Vec4","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"), you can define them in your scenes by using arrays. There are many ways to create the matrix types ("},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftTracer\/documentation\/SwiftTracer\/Mat3"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftTracer\/documentation\/SwiftTracer\/Mat4"},{"text":") which we will also cover in this article.","type":"text"}]},{"style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The scalars are ","type":"text"},{"code":"Float","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and will work with any the following formats.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Exponent: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"7.549790126404332e-08"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"No fractional part: ","type":"text"},{"code":"1","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Normal float: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0.75"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}],"type":"aside"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Vectors","anchor":"Vectors"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For vectors in the form of "},{"code":"(X,Y)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", you can define them as a 2 scalars array."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["{","    \"<Vector property>\": [<X>, <Y>]","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For vectors in the form of "},{"code":"(X,Y,Z)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", you can define them as a 3 scalars array."}]},{"code":["{","    \"<Vector property>\": [<X>, <Y>, <Z>]","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For vectors in the form of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"(X,Y,Z,W)"},{"type":"text","text":", you can define them as a 4 scalars array."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json","code":["{","    \"<Vector property>\": [<X>, <Y>, <Z>, <W>]","}"]},{"level":3,"text":"Matrices","anchor":"Matrices","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Matrices are column based. You can define them with one of the many different forms, depending on what makes more sense for your use case.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"tabs":[{"title":"XYZ","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"XYZ","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" matrices are defined as an optional translation component ","type":"text"},{"code":"o","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(defaults to 0)"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" and the transform parts encoded in 3 optional "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftTracer\/documentation\/SwiftTracer\/Vec3","type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"(defaults to unit vector in the given axis)","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Setting any of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"xyz"},{"text":" values to a unit vector will define the coordinate system, resulting in simple rotations for a camera.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Tip","type":"aside","style":"tip"},{"numberOfColumns":2,"columns":[{"content":[{"syntax":"json","code":["{","    \"o\": [<X>, <Y>, <Z>],","    \"x\": [<X>, <Y>, <Z>]","    \"y\": [<X>, <Y>, <Z>]","    \"z\": [<X>, <Y>, <Z>]","}"],"type":"codeListing"}],"size":1},{"content":[{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["┌                        ┐","│ <X.x>, <X.y>, <X.z>, 0 │","│ <Y.x>, <Y.y>, <Y.z>, 0 │","│ <Z.x>, <Z.y>, <Z.z>, 0 │","│ <O.x>, <O.y>, <O.z>, 1 │","└                        ┘"]}],"size":1}],"type":"row"}]},{"title":"Scale","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Scale","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" matrices are defined as a single scalar for a uniform "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"XYZ"},{"text":" scale factor, or as a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftTracer\/documentation\/SwiftTracer\/Vec3"},{"type":"text","text":" that will become the values of a diagonal matrix."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"row","numberOfColumns":2,"columns":[{"size":1,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Example with a single scalar"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json","code":["{","    \"scale\": <scalar>","}"]}]},{"size":1,"content":[{"type":"codeListing","code":["┌               ┐","│ <s>,  0,   0  │","│  0,  <s>,  0  │","│  0,   0,  <s> │","└               ┘"],"syntax":null}]}]},{"type":"row","numberOfColumns":2,"columns":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Example with a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftTracer\/documentation\/SwiftTracer\/Vec3"}]},{"syntax":"json","type":"codeListing","code":["{","    \"scale\": [<X>, <Y>, <Z>]","}"]}],"size":1},{"content":[{"code":["┌               ┐","│ <X>,  0,   0  │","│  0,  <Y>,  0  │","│  0,   0,  <Z> │","└               ┘"],"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing"}],"size":1}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Axis-Angle"},{"type":"text","text":" matrices are defined as an optional angle in degrees "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"(defaulting to 0)","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and an optional axis around which the rotation occurs (defaulting to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"X"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The axis around which the rotation occurs is equal to 1. The others are equal to 0.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","type":"aside"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json","code":["{","    \"axis\": [0, 0, 1],","    \"angle\": <scalar>","}"]}],"title":"Axis-Angle"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Rotation"},{"type":"text","text":" matrices are defined as a single "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftTracer\/documentation\/SwiftTracer\/Vec3","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" for subsequent yaw pitch roll degrees rotations, following the order of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Y -> X -> Z"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json","code":["{","    \"rotation\": [<X>, <Y>, <Z>]","}"]}],"title":"Rotation"},{"title":"Translate","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Translate"},{"type":"text","text":" matrices are defined as a single "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftTracer\/documentation\/SwiftTracer\/Vec3","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json","code":["{","    \"translate\": [<X>, <Y>, <Z>]","}"]}]},{"title":"Look at","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Look at"},{"text":" matrices are defined as several ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftTracer\/documentation\/SwiftTracer\/Vec3","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" that will get converted into a matrix that looks from at position to a given direction."}]},{"name":"Note","type":"a